osing `}` of the test table at ~line 317):\n\n```go\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"template annotations different\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash1\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash2\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\twantTrue: true,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"template annotations identical\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash1\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash1\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\twantTrue: false,\n\t\t},\n```\n\n---\n\n### Commands to build and test\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-treatment\n\n# Verify it compiles\ngo build ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/...\n\n# Run the unit tests for the istiocsr package\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/... -v -count=1\n\n# Run the specific new tests\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/... -run \"TestComputeCABundleHash|TestReadTrustedCABundle|TestStampCABundleHash\" -v\n\n# Full project build\nmake build\n```\n\n---\n\n### How the idempotency guard works\n\nThe guard has two layers:\n\n1. **Hash-based content comparison**: The SHA-256 is computed from the PEM data, not the `resourceVersion`. Two reconciliation cycles with identical CA bundle content produce the same hash, even if the ConfigMap's `resourceVersion` changed (e.g., from a label update).\n\n2. **Deployment drift detection**: `deploymentSpecModified` now compares `Spec.Template.Annotations`. When the existing deployment already has the same hash annotation as the desired deployment, `hasObjectChanged` returns `false`, and the `UpdateWithRetry` call is skipped entirely (line 51 of `deployments.go`). This is the idempotency guard — no API call is made when the ConfigMap content hasn't changed."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1840,"cache_read_input_tokens":111807,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1840,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"40f75bc1-181a-4148-8afe-533f8e2603b5","uuid":"d5e953b3-9472-40ea-a682-1a56bc414519","timestamp":"2026-07-20T13:32:37.593Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDPiAk4fMeCf7TMTWtp9"}
