CreateCalls` remain.\n\n---\n\n### 9. `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils_test.go` \u2014 add annotation drift test\n\nAdd a test case to `TestDeploymentSpecModified` (insert before the closing `}` of the test table at ~line 317):\n\n```go\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"template annotations different\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash1\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash2\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\twantTrue: true,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"template annotations identical\",\n\t\t\tdesired: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash1\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\tfetched: func() *appsv1.Deployment {\n\t\t\t\td := baseDeployment(1, \"img\")\n\t\t\t\td.Spec.Template.Annotations = map[string]string{caBundleHashAnnotation: \"hash1\"}\n\t\t\t\treturn d\n\t\t\t}(),\n\t\t\twantTrue: false,\n\t\t},\n```\n\n---\n\n### Commands to build and test\n\n```bash\ncd /Users/kpais/kpais-workspace/a_b_evals/repos/cert-manager-operator-treatment\n\n# Verify it compiles\ngo build ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/...\n\n# Run the unit tests for the istiocsr package\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/... -v -count=1\n\n# Run the specific new tests\ngo test ./pkg/controller/istiocsr/... -run \"TestComputeCABundleHash|TestReadTrustedCABundle|TestStampCABundleHash\" -v\n\n# Full project build\nmake build\n```\n\n---\n\n### How the idempotency guard works\n\nThe guard has two layers:\n\n1. **Hash-based content comparison**: The SHA-256 is computed from the PEM data, not the `resourceVersion`. Two reconciliation cycles with identical CA bundle content produce the same hash, even if the ConfigMap's `resourceVersion` changed (e.g., from a label update).\n\n2. **Deployment drift detection**: `deploymentSpecModified` now compares `Spec.Template.Annotations`. When the existing deployment already has the same hash annotation as the desired deployment, `hasObjectChanged` returns `false`, and the `UpdateWithRetry` call is skipped entirely (line 51 of `deployments.go`). This is the idempotency guard \u2014 no API call is made when the ConfigMap content hasn't changed.", "stop_reason": "end_turn", "session_id": "40f75bc1-181a-4148-8afe-533f8e2603b5", "total_cost_usd": 1.3330275, "usage": {"input_tokens": 3370, "cache_creation_input_tokens": 90620, "cache_read_input_tokens": 718105, "output_tokens": 15630, "server_tool_use": {"web_search_requests": 0, "web_fetch_requests": 0}, "service_tier": "standard", "cache_creation": {"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens": 0, "ephemeral_5m_input_tokens": 90620}, "inference_geo": "", "iterations": [], "speed": "standard"}, "modelUsage": {"claude-opus-4-6": {"inputTokens": 3370, "outputTokens": 15630, "cacheReadInputTokens": 718105, "cacheCreationInputTokens": 90620, "webSearchRequests": 0, "costUSD": 1.3330275, "contextWindow": 200000, "maxOutputTokens": 64000}}, "permission_denials": [], "terminal_reason": "completed", "fast_mode_state": "off", "uuid": "b7b0a4e2-8fbc-466b-b222-5ea4f7124293", "timestamp": "2026-07-20T13:32:37.627Z"}